to the editor re past offers little guidance for drought in winter news article march 1 our current water emergency has taken years to develop we have had diminished rain and snowfall for the last three years and our last drought was averted only because of a well timed tropical storm we should begin to think of water as a precious resource unfortunately many only realize this in times of drought water should be conserved at all times not just in times of emergency this would make our water last longer and allow us to better deal with the vagaries of our water supply alexander schoen great neck ny march 1 2002

